node.text:
A tip for your pregnancy 

Do go to sleep on your side in the third trimester

Going to sleep on your back in the third trimester doubles your risk of stillbirth. You may wake up in all sorts of positions during the night, and that’s OK, but if you go to sleep on your side you will be sleeping safely for your baby
.

node.text:
I can’t stop thinking about how last week I was pregnant, and now I’m not. 💔

Admittedly, this was my first miscarriage. And for some reason, because it was a chemical pregnancy, I feel like I’m less qualified to grieve it as a loss. But the truth is, it feels like a loss. Because it is one. 

For four whole days, I was pregnant. I calculated my due date. We made plans to convert our guest bedroom into a nursery. We were so excited to give our kids the greatest gift, a sibling. But then my HCG levels remained at a standstill, and it was all over as quickly as it began. Now, all we have left of this pregnancy is a picture of our embryo and a positive pregnancy test for a baby we will never get to meet earthside
We’re okay, we really are. We’re going to try again next month, and we’re so excited for another chance at baby #3. But all of this is to say, a loss is a loss is a loss, and your grief is valid. ✨
xoxo, Kristyn"
